narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This was a very valuable course that enabled me to read Latin at a faster speed and have a better knowledge of Latin literature.
The place to go for overall knowledge on Roman Literature

Latin Survey is extremely tough but very rewarding. Some weeks, depending on your interests and experience, are easier; some are awful, but ultimately the pace and the amount of material covered make it an incredibly useful course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course helped me prepare for my Latin oral exam and Latin translation exam. I will continue to read but this course gave me a solid foundation.
It helped me a lot in my preparation for the coming Latin exams.

I thought this course was excellent, and I am much more confident about my knowledge of Latin Literature than when I began the semester. I am very pleased with the way my Latin has improved and my ability to understand many texts without a dictionary constantly on hand.
